definitions.definition: Molecules , such as amino acids , sugars , nucleic acids , proteins , polysaccharides , DNA , and RNA , that occur naturally in living organisms ; any such molecule, even if created outside a living thing (as for example in a test tube or bioreactor ).

main_definition: ( biochemistry ) Molecules , such as amino acids , sugars , nucleic acids , proteins , polysaccharides , DNA , and RNA , that occur naturally in living organisms ; any such molecule, even if created outside a living thing (as for example in a test tube or bioreactor ).
